  "text": "Zhu et al. [CITATION_1] found that the JAK2/STAT3 pathway has an important role in the molecular mechanism of SAPinduced acute renal injury and that the suppression of the JAK2/STAT3 pathway could reduce TNF-α and IL-6 plasma levels. In a rat model of SAP-acute lung injury, Han et al. [CITATION_2] demonstrated that dexamethasone treatment suppressed intercellular adhesion molecule-1 mRNA and protein expression via inhibiting IL-6 and TNF-α-induced JAK2/STAT3 activation.",
